WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.690 --> 00:00:04.140
I have a son who is turning 18.

00:00:04.140 --> 00:00:06.630
And three years ago, if you asked me,

00:00:06.630 --> 00:00:09.630
I may force him to major
in computer science.

00:00:09.630 --> 00:00:11.580
He is actually going to the college

00:00:11.580 --> 00:00:14.220
to study commercial dance

00:00:14.220 --> 00:00:17.760
because AI can help people
to do so much of things.

00:00:17.760 --> 00:00:20.220
You basically should pursue your heart.

00:00:20.220 --> 00:00:22.806
You know, just follow your heart.

00:00:22.806 --> 00:00:25.556
(cheerful music)

00:00:27.750 --> 00:00:30.000
Genspark is the all in one workspace.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.723
We do AI spreadsheets,
AI slides, AI documents,

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:37.683
all kind of work for normal
white collar workers.

00:00:40.890 --> 00:00:43.440
When you think about
how we work together,

00:00:43.440 --> 00:00:45.480
the applied AI team and Genspark,

00:00:45.480 --> 00:00:47.010
what's it like on your side

00:00:47.010 --> 00:00:49.080
when you get something new from us?

00:00:49.080 --> 00:00:51.600
All our engineers are very curious about

00:00:51.600 --> 00:00:54.390
the latest advancement
for the latest models,

00:00:54.390 --> 00:00:55.920
so every time we got this request,

00:00:55.920 --> 00:00:58.320
it's kind of like a
invitation to the party,

00:00:58.320 --> 00:00:59.970
so we enjoyed it a lot.

00:00:59.970 --> 00:01:01.380
We are a very small startup,

00:01:01.380 --> 00:01:03.480
so we cannot do everything by ourself,

00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:05.640
and working with kind of trusted partner

00:01:05.640 --> 00:01:07.020
is really, really important.

00:01:07.020 --> 00:01:09.090
What do you think are
the things that you do

00:01:09.090 --> 00:01:11.460
that make you unique and help you succeed?

00:01:11.460 --> 00:01:13.680
Everybody is talking
about mode these days.

00:01:13.680 --> 00:01:18.240
I don't really think nowadays
anybody have any mode

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:20.370
because everything is happening so fast.

00:01:20.370 --> 00:01:22.380
The only mode is the team's culture.

00:01:22.380 --> 00:01:23.940
We always exploring

00:01:23.940 --> 00:01:25.800
and trying the newest technology

00:01:25.800 --> 00:01:27.631
to execute faster.

00:01:27.631 --> 00:01:30.900
(cheerful music)

00:01:30.900 --> 00:01:32.940
In the collaboration,
the openness is the key.

00:01:32.940 --> 00:01:36.390
The sum of the secret you
kept today will be worthless,

00:01:36.390 --> 00:01:37.773
you know, tomorrow.

00:01:38.850 --> 00:01:40.290
The success of the partnership,

00:01:40.290 --> 00:01:43.890
it comes to deep neutral trust.

00:01:43.890 --> 00:01:47.970
When it's really working,
it's very tight feedback loop.

00:01:47.970 --> 00:01:50.340
I just did an interview yesterday

00:01:50.340 --> 00:01:51.547
and the candidate asked me

00:01:51.547 --> 00:01:53.970
"What will Genspark be in two years?"

00:01:53.970 --> 00:01:55.830
My answer is, I don't know.

00:01:55.830 --> 00:01:58.830
A lot of new things will happen

00:01:58.830 --> 00:02:01.824
and it will even seem like magic.

00:02:01.824 --> 00:02:04.574
(cheerful music)

